      "The Hebrew man's question — 'Who made you a ruler and judge over us?' — challenges Moses' assumed authority. How do you earn the right to lead people who haven't asked for your leadership?",
      "Moses names his son 'Stranger.' What does it feel like to belong nowhere, and can that displacement ever become a gift?",
      "Why do you think God let Moses spend forty years in the desert before calling him? What was being formed in that silence?",
      "How do you distinguish between righteous anger that leads to justice and reactive anger that leads to more harm?"
